        <content><![CDATA[    <h1 class="title topictitle1">Create actual business services during planning</h1>        <div class="body taskbody">        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step stepexpand">                <span class="ph cmd">Collect the following data and enter it in this form:</span>                <div class="itemgroup info">                    <ul class="ul" id="sa_dw_business_service-normal__ul_nb1_swd_lw"><li class="li">The name of the business service.</li><li class="li">The name of the service deployment owner. <span class="ph">The service                    deployment owner is responsible for creating and fixing business services during                    planning.</span>                        </li><li class="li">Entry points. <span class="ph">An entry point is a property of a connection to a                    configuration item (CI). </span>                        </li></ul>                </div>            </li><li class="li step stepexpand">                <span class="ph cmd">Test connectivity for the entry points.</span>            </li><li class="li step stepexpand">                <span class="ph cmd">Create an actual business service:</span>                <div class="itemgroup info">A user with the sm_admin role and defined as the service deployment owner for                    this business service completes this step.</div>                <ol class="ol substeps" id="sa_dw_business_service-normal__substeps_lx1_422_lw"><li class="li substep">                        <span class="ph cmd">Click <span class="ph uicontrol">Create and Discover</span>.</span>                    </li><li class="li substep">                        <span class="ph cmd">Enter the name of the application owner. <span class="ph">The application owner is familiar with the                    infrastructure and applications making up the service. This user provides                    information necessary for successful mapping of a business service. Once a                    service is mapped, this user reviews the results and either approves it or                    suggests changes.</span></span>                    </li><li class="li substep">                        <span class="ph cmd">Click <span class="ph uicontrol">Send for Review</span>.</span>                    </li></ol>            </li><li class="li step stepexpand">                <span class="ph cmd">Review and approve the business service:</span>                <div class="itemgroup info">A user with the sm_app_owner role and defined as the application owner for                    this business service completes this step.</div>                <ol class="ol substeps" id="sa_dw_business_service-normal__substeps_amt_522_lw"><li class="li substep">                        <span class="ph cmd">Click <span class="ph uicontrol">View Map</span> and review the map.</span>                    </li><li class="li substep">                        <span class="ph cmd">Enter your comments in the <span class="ph uicontrol">Notes</span> field.</span>                    </li><li class="li substep">                        <span class="ph cmd">If the mapping results are satisfactory, click                                <span class="ph uicontrol">Approve</span>.</span>                    </li></ol>            </li></ol>    </div>    <div class="related-links"><div class="relinfo"><div class="reltitle">Related information<br /><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:creation-actual-services-planning&amp;version&#61;jakarta" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Creation of actual business services during planning</a></div><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:plan-business-services&amp;version&#61;jakarta" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Plan business services</a></div></div></div></div>]]></content>
